          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-7867 osd-ldiskfs: compatible check for IDIF OI consistency",
        "message": "LU-7867 osd-ldiskfs: compatible check for IDIF OI consistency\n\nFor old IDIF, the OST index is not part of the IDIF, means the IDIF in\nLMA EA does not contain the OST index, but the IDIF used for locating\nthe OST-object may contains OST index, such difference would misguide\nthe OSD to reguard the IDIF OI mapping invalid as to trigger OI scrub\nunexpectedly. The right solution is to make some compatible check to\ndistinguish whether the invalid IDIF OI mapping is caused by OST index\nissue or not to avoid triggered OI scrub unnecessarily.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I1fba55064396850bc9634c6689d38f4683c3b75e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
